claim: Flublok (quadrivalent) was evaluated in the pivotal trial against Fluarix (quadrivalent standard-dose vaccine).
explanation: The figure is a two‐panel bar/line plot showing the proportion of participants achieving ≥4‐fold increases in hemagglutination inhibition titers against cell‐grown vaccine virus strains in two age groups (18–44 and 45–64 years). For each strain (A(H3N2), A(H1N1)pdm09, B/VIC, B/YAM), pre‐ and post‐vaccination values are plotted for seven vaccine sequence groups: ccIIV4-ccIIV4, ccIIV4-RIV4, RIV4-ccIIV4, RIV4-RIV4, IIV4-ccIIV4, IIV4-RIV4, and IIV4-Fluzone IIV4. does not support the claim because the figure compares cell-based (ccIIV4), recombinant (RIV4, i.e. Flublok), and egg-based Fluzone IIV4 sequences but does not include Fluarix (quadrivalent) as a comparator. Note: The figure legend and labels are clear; no mention of Fluarix IIV4 is visible.
